{title: Song For The Mira}
{artist: Anne Murray}
{composer: Written by Allister MacGillivray}

[G]Out on the [C]Mira one warm [G]afternoon
[D7]Old men go [G]fishing with [C]black line and [D7]spoon
[G]And if they catch [C]nothing they never [G]complain
I wish I was [D7]with them [G]again
As boys in their boats call to [C]girls on the [G]shore
[D7]Teasing the [G]one that they [C]dearly [D7]adore
[G]And into the evening [C]the courting [G]begins
I wish I was [D7]with them [G]again
[C]Can you imagine a [G]piece of the universe
[D7]More fit for princes and [G]kings
[C]I'll trade you ten of your [G]cities
For Marion [A7]Bridge and the pleasure it [D7]brings
[G]Out on the [C]Mira on soft [G]summer nights
[D7]Bonfires [G]blaze to the [C]children's [D7]delight
[G]They dance round flames singing [C]songs with their [G]friends
I wish I was [D7]with them [G]again
Repeat #3
[G]Now I'll conclude with a [C]wish you go [G]well
[D7]Sweet be your [G]dreams and your [C]happiness [D7]swell
[G]I'll leave you here for my [C]journey be[G]gins
I'm going to be [D7]with them [G]going to be [D7]with them
I'm [G]going to be [D7]with them [G]again
Repeat #3